  <bioghist id="aspace_18bfdac144ec574d57abd77031083c89">
    <head>History</head>
<p>This synagogue, originally named Kaiser Torah, was founded at the corner of Webster Avenue and Erin Street in the Hill District, Pittsburgh, Pa. In 1922, it changed its name to Congregation Kether Torah, and later, in the 1950s, moved to Bartlett Street in Squirrel Hill, Pittsburgh, Pa.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_026331eda07e41eaffb6cfb108251670">
    <head>Scope and Content Notes</head>
<p>This collection contains miscellaneous records including: history, charter, by-laws, membership lists from c. 1960, minutes of eight congregational meetings between 1927 and 1939, papers concerning the sale of the synagogue property in the Hill District, blueprint and legal documents concerning cemetery in Reserve Township, Pa., some general correspondence and a blueprint of synagogue from c. 1913.</p>  </scopecontent>
